FT  09 MAR 93 / Sarajevo citizens dodge bullets
Defying danger: heavy gunfire from Serb snipers forces people to run for
cover in the Bosnian capital of Sarajevo. Shots were hitting the wall as
shoppers and workers crouched and dashed past. Bosnia's army commander,
General Sefir Halilovic, yesterday ordered his forces to launch a
counter-offensive against Bosnian Serb troops in the east of the country 'to
prevent the massacre of innocent people' in besieged Moslem enclaves
following a 10-day assault
Bosnian push ordered, Page 2; Serbs to face UN pressure on peace plan, Page
2
